What is the output of the following pseudocode?
function Mystery(x):
  if x <= 0: return 0
  if x == 1: return 1
  return Mystery(x-1) + Mystery(x-2)
Print Mystery(4)

Consider the pseudocode:
function WhatIsThis(arr, n):
  if n <= 0: return 0
  return arr[n-1] + WhatIsThis(arr, n-1)

What does WhatIsThis([1, 2, 3, 4], 4) return?
